description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;Make a difference from day one!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Are you collaborative, caring and compassionate?&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; Prisons are one of the most challenging, yet rewarding places for healthcare professionals to work. If you’re looking for a role where you can develop your existing skills and learn something new every day, then this is the place to be.&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; As a healthcare provider, we recognise the fact that prisoners are a socially excluded group with complex healthcare needs that can often be associated with poor outcomes. We believe in putting the patient first, regardless of the environment or their history.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;About the role&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be an integral part of the Substance Misuse Team for service users with complex drug related needs within HMP Highpoint. You will assist the Senior Nurse manage a caseload of service users, liaising with other drug/alcohol and associated users to promote harm minimisation. You will also support secondary screening services within the one stop shop as substance misuse support.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About you&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will have evidence of clinical training with experience of undertaking risk assessments and management of vulnerable client groups. Experience of working with individuals who have drug and alcohol problems in a clinical setting is also essential. You must be able to work independently and as part of a multidisciplinary team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;In return for your hard work you will...&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Receive an annual salary of up to £25,500 FTE - dependent on experience. You&#39;ll also get a number of benefits including a company contributory pension scheme, 25 days annual leave plus 8 public bank holidays plus CPD and re-validation support.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Other benefits include cycle to work scheme, childcare vouchers plus training and clinical development opportunities. Onsite benefits at HMP Highpoint include access to an onsite gym, free parking and subsidised mess/canteen.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Skills &amp; Experience&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We could give you the opportunity to develop in to a specialist role of your interest and benefit to the service i.e. ANP, BBV, sexual health, plastering, ILS/ALS (intermediate life support and advanced life support), health promotion, phlebotomy, vaccinations, suturing, wound care, RCGP, and long term condition courses.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An understanding of Health in justice services and the interface with both prisons and the wider healthcare service available to prisoners is beneficial. You should have the ability to easily translate theory in to practice, and comprehensive knowledge of legislative procedures, governing care and treatment of mentally disordered patients.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Next Steps&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are shortlisted, you will be contacted by Basanti Lama, the Internal Recruiter for this role. The recruiter will submit your CV to the hiring manager and in turn Basanti will arrange an interview for you to attend at HMP Highpoint if the hiring manager feels that you are suitable for the job.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please note that this role is subject to Practice Plus Group Terms &amp; Conditions and offers of employment are subject to satisfactory receipt of references, enhanced DBS check and prison vetting.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At Practice Plus Group we actively promote diversity and equal opportunities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;This job advert will close as soon as a sufficient number of suitable applications have been received. Please apply for this job as soon as you can, if interested.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
